## Phase 2 — WhatsApp Integration & Onboarding (Days 7–12)

### TASK-009 · Twilio WhatsApp Webhook

**Files**
- `server/src/routes/webhook.js`
- `server/src/controllers/webhookController.js`
- `server/src/middleware/twilioAuth.js`

**Steps**
1. `npm install twilio`
2. `twilioAuth.js` — validates `X-Twilio-Signature` header using Twilio SDK
3. `webhookController.js` — parses Twilio POST body, extracts `From`, `Body`
4. On valid request: logs `{ from, body }` and replies `200 OK`
5. Register `POST /webhook/whatsapp` route

**Acceptance Criteria**
- [ ] A valid Twilio webhook POST returns 200
- [ ] An invalid signature (wrong header) returns 403
- [ ] Parsed `from` and `body` are logged to console
- [ ] Test using `curl` or Twilio sandbox

